ok, I think we need to address the missing callback as in this PR.  https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ai/pull/2931  

we need a new issue for that.

as for the original issue, what about this naming scheme?

**current**

```
	ChatClientRequestSpec tools(String... toolNames);

		ChatClientRequestSpec tools(ToolCallback... toolCallbacks);

		ChatClientRequestSpec tools(List<ToolCallback> toolCallbacks);

		ChatClientRequestSpec tools(Object... toolObjects);

		ChatClientRequestSpec tools(ToolCallbackProvider... toolCallbackProviders);
```


**proposed**


```
ChatClientRequestSpec tools(Object... toolObjects);

ChatClientRequestSpec toolNames(String... toolNames);




// For ToolCallback varargs - specific callback implementations 
ChatClientRequestSpec toolCallbacks(ToolCallback... toolCallbacks);

// For List of ToolCallback - similar to above but as a collection
ChatClientRequestSpec toolCallbacks(List<ToolCallback> toolCallbacks);


// For ToolCallbackProvider varargs - factory/provider pattern
ChatClientRequestSpec toolCallbacks(ToolCallbackProvider... toolCallbackProviders);
```

issues.body:
Here is my relevant code：

  ```
  public ChatClient chatClient(AiChatOptions options) {
        OpenAiApi openAiApi = OpenAiApi.builder()
                .apiKey(options.getApiKey())
                .baseUrl(options.getBaseUrl())
                .build();

        ToolCallback[] customerTools = ToolCallbacks.from(new DateTimeTool());


        OpenAiChatModel chatModel = OpenAiChatModel.builder()
                .openAiApi(openAiApi)
                .defaultOptions(OpenAiChatOptions.builder()
                        .model(options.getModelType())
                        .toolCallbacks(customerTools)
                        .build())
                .build();

        return ChatClient.create(chatModel);
    }

```

```
 public String execute() {
            LogUtils.info("Processing chat request for messages: {}", messages);
            return chatClient.prompt(messages.getFirst())
                    .tools(new DateTimeTool())
                    .call()
                    .content();
        }
```

The relevant prompts are consistent with the documentation, but after testing, the response was directly returned by the main model without calling the tool.

